      "writtenOn": "2020-12-30T18:21:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "No, this is a long-term feature, for the reasons I documented in doc.go and the design doc. I believe it\u0027s important to be able to run this code without a Build in context (like, for example, as a CLI application). Otherwise you\u0027d have to write \"recipe code\" and \"normal code\" as two separate efforts. This way you can write a program or library as normal code, and then sprinkle steps in the middle without rendering that code useless outside the context of a build.\n\nIt also means that you can write tests for your code without setting up a Build, which I think will be useful.",
